{
  "__comment": "EDIS Z2 top-level overview. Service health: because every EDIS service ships metrics via OTLP through the single otel-collector (not a per-service Prometheus scrape), Prometheus's own `up` only reflects the collector/redpanda/prometheus scrape targets (see deploy/prometheus/prometheus.yml). Per-service liveness is therefore derived from whether a service is emitting metrics: count(group by (service_name)(...)) over a service-stamped metric (service.name -> service_name label via the collector's resource_to_telemetry_conversion). edis_service_up is an ASPIRATIONAL per-service heartbeat gauge named sensibly; until services register it, the 'EDIS services emitting telemetry' panel falls back to counting distinct service_name labels on llm/ingest/processing metrics. KPI tiles reuse the same metric names as the other three dashboards.",
  "annotations": {
    "list": [
      {
        "builtIn": 1,
        "datasource": { "type": "grafana", "uid": "-- Grafana --" },
        "enable": true,
        "hide": true,
